"{\"key\":\"learned-opencode-commands-are-fully-supported-via-config-opencode\",\"type\":\"learned\",\"content\":\"OpenCode commands are fully supported via ~/.config/opencode/commands/*.md files (accessed via Ctrl+K). Each .md file becomes a command with filename as ID. Support named arguments with \\\\$PLACEHOLDER syntax. Commands CAN be ported - created bdcompound-xr3 to track.\",\"source\":\"user\",\"tags\":[\"learned\",\"config\"],\"ts\":1771035459,\"bead\":\"bdcompound-18w\"}"
"{\"key\":\"learned-opencode-plugin-ts-uses-bun-spawn-not-shell-template-to\",\"type\":\"learned\",\"content\":\"OpenCode plugin.ts uses Bun.spawn() not $ shell template to prevent command injection. Pre-fork filtering of bd comments regex in TypeScript avoids subprocess overhead on 95% of bash commands.\",\"source\":\"user\",\"tags\":[\"learned\",\"typescript\"],\"ts\":1771034694,\"bead\":\"bdcompound-a3a\"}"
